Actually, no, you wouldn't see much of an improvement.  Odd thing about mage id bracer is, you have to have the lvl 44 summon to affect our lvl 39 spells.  Mages don't get a lvl 39 nuke, so their ID bracer only works up to lvl 34 until they get their lvl 44 spells.  <br>
<br>
I remember being in a similar group in OT and just using the mage ID focused lvl 34 nuke instead of the one we got at lvl 39 because the ID focused nuke ended up being pretty darn close, so it was more mana efficient.  Unless you go all out and chain nuke, this means a mage can outburn a wizard in these level ranges. <br>
<br>
Our lvl 39 dd is really weak. <br>
