<br>
Allow me to qualify my statement, though, if I may.  Most groups in the level range the original poster discussed (indeed, basically anything pre-50) don't often have the organization or skills to handle a multi-mob pull well enough to position the mobs so they can be hit by our column/pillar spells.  <br>
<br>
A guild group/raid, as you mentioned, that was well organized, and most likely 50+, would be better able to handle such a situation, and I could definitely see using that spell line in those circumstances.  Twinks and alts might be able to organize such a thing pre-50, though...  I won't say I've never used them in a group, but it has been very rare for me to use them outside of quadding.<br>
<br>
<br>
Of course (and give this point the least weight, as it's not applicable to 90% of the EQ population), I'm on a PvP server, and AEs in groups can sometimes hit my own group members, so that's a further restriction.  But that's a minor point.<br>
<br>
<br>
In any case, that still leaves wizards with at best, 2 lines of useful spells in the 1-49 game.  The Al-Kabor's never get better, and channeling skill is level-limited to prevent PBAEs from being terribly useful pre-50, and pre-50 rains have useless ratios.  I agree with the original poster that some of our spell lines (pre-50) could stand to be looked at, and I wouldn't mind seeing a mini-spear line extend down to the lower levels (a la Frozen Harpoon).  With the KEI fix, perhaps SOE will consider taking a look at them.  /crosses fingers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=necridious>Necridious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 359<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 10:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lvl 39 spells</span><hr size=1> Well, pre 50 rains do have one advantage for the low level caster-- they don't draw as much aggro, which, without Concussion they need to really stay on top of the aggro control.<br>
