<br>
When KEI was able to be casted on me (level 1-40) I could out aggo any melee person when I had at least 20% mana, regardless of how tweaked they are.  Why does that matter?  Chain nuking is the fastest way to do damage and the way to get the most damage in.  With KEI, this was our real constraint in a group.  Now, without KEI, my constraint is my mana regen.  This has lowered my damage output at my early 40's.<br>
<br>
So, what's my point?  If they gave KEI back to mid-level wizards it would bring them a bit closer into balance with their tweaked melee counterparts.  Other then under level 20, I think we can all agree that KEI made life easier for wizards and put us on par with melee tweaks about the same level.  That said, I agree with the KEI 'nerf' even though I really hate it.<br>
<br>
Why is that?  Look at a Paladin/Ranger/Cleric/Shaman/Druid at the mid level game with KEI.  With 'free' mana, the Paladin/Ranger has virtually no downtime because they should have near full mana at the end of a fight to heal themselves up to full, then regen while fighting.  Maybe it's not quite as good as I'm saying, but KEI on low level casting melees that can heal is over-powering.  Now, what about the Cleric/Shaman/Druid?  With healers having no mana constraints, the group can pull and pull and pull and pull and pull.  That, again, is over powering.  There is no cap like wizards have with aggo.<br>
<br>
So, no KEI really sucks for wizards because it was actually somewhat balanced for us.  But I agree with the change because of healers with KEI was making the tweaked melee so much more powerful (especially when the tweaked melee could heal themselves).<br>
<br>
At 46+ KEI is still really only a great boon for wizards and druids.  We can bind somewhere fairly safe, port out, get KEI, gate back, and re-join the group.  Others must take more time to get a refresh which means they either don't get a refresh, loose valuable time and possibly their place in the group, or are limited in hunting groups that are fairly close to PoK book (errm, anyone ever wonder why LoY is so sparsely populated... that's right KEI.)<br>
<br>
Ok, last but not least, can someone send me a link to &quot;Damage Parsing for Dummies&quot;?  I think I want to start running my own experiments and post it in that other forum there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilsainsilverback>Pilsain Silverback</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 938<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 10:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tweaked mid-lvl Paladin spanks lower lvl wizard in dmg.</span><hr size=1> I'm not overly concerned about whether or not I can outdamage another class in a group.  We are, to a degree, bound by the hate list.<br>
