(7)  Did you add the pets special attack into damage?  No you couldn't have because no parser shows it (so when we look at damage of the mage not taking this into account always makes me laugh my ass off since I'm a 65 mage.  Water pet doing 160 lure DD every 6 seconds adds up to a shit ton).<br>
<br>
So in conclusion there are alot of variables.  (A)Twinking casters is not nearly as good as twinking melee (efficiency wise).  Once again a game design flaw. (B) You're logs don't show everything. (C) The most efficient way to twink casters is with a horse and KEI and you have rightly pointed out that the lack of KEI has hurt casters.  Good now how about some love for the lower end casters then since focus items don't compensate for giving a melee a fungi, a CoCW/CoF, and a good weapon (pick one). (D) Wizards in particular don't come into there own until later in the game (bad design but that's how it is), then they are a terror.  They are supposedly compensated by greater ease of soloing though (can be argued I know).  So if your point was to demonstrate that in the lower end game (1-50) that casters need some help Vs their twinked melee bretheren you have reaffirmed what we all know. Grats!<br>
<br>
I will say though, speaking from experience that at 44, even with no kei but using shock of swords and focused 44 water or fire pet that you couldn't possibly do the damage that the mage is doing--especially with his new DS included.  And when he gets to 49 he far and away kicks your ass by a wide margin.  I think the designers realize this and that's how they decide game balance by how the character does over its life rather than in ranges.<br>
<br>
Btw, the most damaging character in that group would have been the enchanter if you chose to charm.  With creativity and skill come effectiveness.  The least damaging character in your parse could have not only been doing the most additive damage via haste but also direct damage with a dual wielding, hasted charmed mob.  Something to think about. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=darkpaktgrimsoul>Darkpakt Grimsoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 653<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 12:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tweaked mid-lvl Paladin spanks lower lvl wizard in dmg.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And like you said, you had damage shields, and no proper way to give credit where credit is due. Is your damage amount including the damage shields? You don't say if your damage includes that or not. I'm thinking, it does. Most melees I know always say, Look I was doing x amount of damage each time I got hit!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
